description: This Conversation provides answers to questions about the SMS feature of Voice Gateway for Watson.

next_step.dialog_node: where are the docs
would you like to know more

values: When acting as a Contact center agent initiates SMS sessions: In this scenario, the SMS agent plays a supporting role to a telephone-based contact center. In a typical environment, a contact center agent that is assisting a customer over the phone can start an SMS session and hand the customer over to the SMS agent. From there, the SMS agent can further assist the customer. By offloading some customer interaction to the SMS agent, the contact center can handle increased call volumes. When acting as a Customer initiates SMS sessions: The SMS agent can also operate independently if you enable customers to contact the SMS agent directly in the configuration. In this scenario, the SMS agent provides assistance without any human intervention. This approach is beneficial for customers who prefer to interact over SMS messages rather than voice calls, such as when they have a quick question. Do you have any more questions about this feature of voice gateway?
OK.

next_step.dialog_node: end call

values: The sms fetaure of Voice Gateway is architected as an independent scalable micro service. To be able to deploy this micro service you need a Docker environment such as IBM Cloud private. This can either be on premises or in a cloud of your choosing. Note that although the voice gateway can be run in either location, the Watson Conversion service which it communicates with is only available in the cloud in IBM Bluemix. values: I use the watson speech to text service to transcribe what you are saying, and the text to speech service to speak back to you. The conversation service is fed the transcript of what you are saying, and by using a combination of natural language processing, and rules which guide me to the correct responses, I am able to find an appropriate response for your questions. The retrieve and rank service is used when I am in agent assist mode, and is used to ensure that the information I send to a call centre agent is the most relevant information for the current conversation
